A.Name: Agilent Technologies Inc
A.Description: Agilent Technologies, Inc. is a premier American company headquartered in Santa Clara, California, specializing in analytical instrumentation and life sciences solutions. Renowned for its innovative products and services, Agilent caters to diverse markets including scientific research, diagnostics, and quality control, thereby reinforcing its position as a vital contributor to the global analytical economy. The company's extensive portfolio encompasses cutting-edge instruments and software, enabling advancements in life sciences and applied chemical sectors. With a steadfast commitment to innovation and customer-centric strategies, Agilent is poised to meet the evolving needs of its clients across various industries, making it a compelling investment opportunity for institutional investors.

GBLI.Name: Global Indemnity Group, LLC Class A Common Stock
GBLI.Description: Global Indemnity PLC is a leading diversified insurance provider, focusing on property and casualty coverage for both individual and commercial clients throughout the United States, as well as offering reinsurance solutions worldwide. Based in Bala Cynwyd, Pennsylvania, the company utilizes its deep industry knowledge to develop customized insurance products that meet the distinct needs of its policyholders. Committed to sustainable growth and innovation, Global Indemnity strives to generate long-term value for its stakeholders while adhering to disciplined underwriting standards.

AAP.Name: Advance Auto Parts Inc
AAP.Description: Advance Auto Parts, Inc. (AAP) is a prominent aftermarket automotive parts and accessories retailer in the United States, serving both professional installers and do-it-yourself consumers. Based in Raleigh, North Carolina, the company boasts a comprehensive network of retail stores and distribution centers that streamline product availability and delivery. With a strong commitment to customer satisfaction, Advance Auto Parts differentiates itself through a broad selection of high-quality automotive components and innovative technological solutions, including e-commerce integration, which enhances its competitive position within the dynamic automotive aftermarket sector. As the industry continues to evolve, AAP is well-equipped to capitalize on growth opportunities driven by increasing vehicle complexity and consumer demand for quality auto service.

AAL.Name: American Airlines Group
AAL.Description: American Airlines Group Inc. (AAL), headquartered in Fort Worth, Texas, is the preeminent airline holding company globally, recognized for its extensive network that serves millions of passengers across domestic and international routes. By combining a modern fleet with advanced technology, AAL prioritizes operational efficiency and exceptional customer service, setting industry standards for flight performance and traveler satisfaction. The company is steadfast in its commitment to sustainability, actively pursuing initiatives to minimize its environmental impact. As a publicly traded entity, American Airlines Group maintains a strong emphasis on driving shareholder value while strategically navigating growth opportunities in the dynamic airline industry.
AAL.Address: 1 SKYVIEW DRIVE, FORT WORTH, TX, UNITED STATES, 76155

AAPL.Name: Apple Inc
AAPL.Description: Apple Inc. is a leading American multinational technology company that specializes in innovative consumer electronics, software, and online services. With a record revenue of $274.5 billion in 2020, it holds the title of the world's most valuable publicly traded company and is a dominant force in the global technology landscape. Its flagship products, such as the iPhone, iPad, and Mac, have cemented its reputation as a trailblazer in the sector, positioning it as the fourth-largest PC vendor and smartphone manufacturer worldwide. As a cornerstone of the "Big Five" technology companies, Apple continues to set industry standards and drive advancements in technology and consumer engagement.
AAPL.Address: ONE APPLE PARK WAY, CUPERTINO, CA, UNITED STATES, 95014

NVDA.Name: NVIDIA Corporation
NVDA.Description: NVIDIA Corporation is a prominent American multinational technology firm based in Santa Clara, California, recognized for its leadership in the design and manufacturing of advanced graphics processing units (GPUs) for gaming and professional markets. The company is at the cutting edge of AI and visual computing technologies, developing critical solutions such as System on a Chip (SoC) products that enhance mobile computing and automotive applications, particularly in the expanding field of autonomous driving. With a diverse portfolio that encompasses gaming, data centers, and AI infrastructure, NVIDIA is committed to delivering innovative products and services that meet the demands of a dynamic technology landscape.

GOOG.Name: Alphabet Inc Class C
GOOG.Description: Alphabet Inc. (GOOG) is a premier American multinational conglomerate headquartered in Mountain View, California, established in October 2015 as part of Google's corporate restructuring. As the parent company of Google and a diverse array of subsidiaries, Alphabet operates at the forefront of technology across key sectors, including search services, advertising, cloud computing, consumer electronics, and artificial intelligence. Renowned for its substantial revenue generation, the company plays a crucial role in the evolution of the global digital economy. With its co-founders actively involved in leadership, Alphabet is well-positioned to drive innovative solutions and expand its influence in emerging technology markets.

META.Name: Meta Platforms Inc.
META.Description: Meta Platforms, Inc. is a leading technology firm based in Menlo Park, California, renowned for transforming social connectivity through its flagship platforms, including Facebook, Instagram, and WhatsApp. Pioneering developments in virtual and augmented reality via its Reality Labs division, Meta is at the forefront of the metaverse, exploring innovative consumer engagement avenues. By significantly investing in immersive technologies, the company not only attracts a large, diverse user base but also enhances its advertising revenue, thereby reinforcing its position as a dominant force in the rapidly evolving digital landscape.

AMD.Name: Advanced Micro Devices Inc
AMD.Description: Advanced Micro Devices, Inc. (AMD) is a prominent American semiconductor company based in Santa Clara, California, renowned for its innovative microprocessors, graphics processors, and motherboard chipsets. Catering to diverse markets, including data centers, enterprise solutions, and consumer electronics, AMD's commitment to high-performance computing has positioned it as a significant force in the rapidly evolving semiconductor industry. MPW.Description: Medical Properties Trust, Inc. The company partners with top-tier healthcare operators to ensure the delivery of essential inpatient care, maintaining a diversified portfolio that positions it well to capitalize on the increasing demand for healthcare services.
